    <Descriptive_Notes>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Section containing around 10 species of large, deciduous that are indigenous to North America and eastern Asia. They are distinguished buds emitting a balsam scent, by leaves having a white underside, and by a leaf petiole that is round in cross-section rather than flattened.</Note_Text>
